Start by making the whipped honey cinnamon butter to have ready for serving. Place @salted butter{0.5%cup} in a medium bowl. Using a hand or stand mixer, beat on high for 2 minutes. Then, add in @powdered sugar{0.375%cup}, @honey{2%tbsp}, @cinnamon{1.5%tsp}, and @vanilla extract{0.25%tsp}, and beat on high until well combined and fluffy. Save some at room temp to serve with the crepes. Then, transfer the rest to a jar or container and store in the fridge.

Then make the crepes. In a large bowl, whisk together @sourdough discard{1%cup}, @milk{0.5%cup}, @egg yolks{3%yolks}, @granulated sugar{2%tsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, and @olive oil{1.5%tsp}. Heat a large #skillet{} over medium-low heat. Once heated, lightly grease with @butter{1%tbsp}. Using a 1/3 cup measuring cup, pour the batter into the bottom of the skillet. Gently lift the pan and move it in a circular motion until the batter is spread evenly around the bottom. Cook the crepe for ~{1%minute|2%minutes}. Once the top isnâ€™t glossy and the crepe is ready to slip, use a spatula to gently lift the edge, and flip it over. Cook for another ~{1%minute|2%minutes}, until lightly golden. Then, slide the crepe onto a plate. Repeat with the remaining batter.

Serve warm with the whipped honey cinnamon butter, whipped cream, and powdered sugar, if desired.
